medical_history.chief_complaint: Periumbilical pain that localizes to the suprapubic region.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 24 hours ago, initially periumbilical pain which progressed to suprapubic localization. Pain did not improve with Tums and omeprazole. Associated symptoms include dizziness, chills, non-productive emesis, headache, and anorexia.
